ENTRY            F1100   20260108   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F1100001   20260108   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 10         24
TITLE      Elastic and inelastic scattering of protons on Sm-148,
           Sm-154, and Yb-174
AUTHOR     (A.B.Kurepin,B.Madsen,B.Albek)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSLEB,2DENNBI)
REFERENCE  (J,BAS,31,174,1968) English translation
           (J,IZV,31,195,1967)
FACILITY   (VDG,2DENNBI)
DETECTOR   (TELES,SIBAR) The telescopic system consisting of two
           dE/dx counters and one E surface barrier silicon
           counter was used.
SAMPLE     Free film was used as a target.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S,2.,5.) An error of elastic scattering cross
           section at the angles more than 30 degr. was 2-3% and
           at the angle of 20 degr. it was 5%. Accuracy of peak
           separation, elastic scattering background, statistics,
           and in some cases contribution of impurities were
           taken into account. Only in some cases the errors
           exceed 10%. Inelastic cross section measurements
           were characterized by smaller errors (2-4%) due to
           the less contribution of elastic scattering.
           (ERR-1) An error of the absolute normalization
METHOD     (EDE)
HISTORY    (20110324C)
           (20260108A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              24
COMMON               2          3
EN         ERR-1
MEV        PER-CENT
        12.         4.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           31
